由于缺乏疫苗等应对措施和其他未知因素的存在，专家们仍认为疫情对美国构成风险文 | 《巴伦》撰稿人列什玛·卡帕迪亚编辑 | 郭力群虽然投资者对于新冠病毒疫情造成的后果的担忧正在减弱，但一些顶尖医学专家警告称，由于缺乏疫苗等应对措施和其他未知因素的存在，他们仍认为疫情对美国来说是一种风险。
Experts say the outbreak poses a risk to the U.S. because of a lack of responses such as a vaccine and other unknown factors. While investors are becoming less worried about the consequences of the new crown virus epidemic, some leading medical experts warn that they still believe it is a risk for the U.S. because of a lack of a vaccine and other unknown factors.
目前全球范围的感染人数已经超过六万人，死亡人数超过一千人，大多数病例出现在疫情中心武汉市。
More than 60,000 people have been infected and more than a thousand have died worldwide, most of them in Wuhan, the epicentre of the epidemic.
人们对这种病毒目前还知之甚少。
Little is known about the virus.
非营利组织、美国著名学术研究机构阿斯彭研究所(Aspen Institute)周二（2月11日）在华盛顿举办了一场小组讨论会，与会者都是疫情防控方面的专家。
Aspen Institute, a leading US academic and research organization, held a panel discussion in Washington on Tuesday, February 11, attended by experts in disease control.
以下是他们对美国面临的风险、疫苗研发前景以及这次疫情和过去发生过的疫情的对比等问题的看法。
Here are their views on the risks facing the United States, the prospects for vaccine development, and the comparison of the epidemic with past outbreaks.
美国面临的风险有多大？美国疾病控制与预防中心(Centers for Disease Control and Prevention)下属的国家免疫和呼吸系统疾病中心(National Center for Immune and Respiratory Diseases)主任南希·梅松尼耶(Nancy Messonnier)博士称，“目前美国面临的风险很低，因为我们还没有看到任何疫情蔓延的迹象。
'There is very little risk in the U.S. right now because we don't see any signs of spreading, 'says Nancy Messonnier, director of the National Center for Immune and Respiratory Diseases, which is part of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.
”到目前为止，美国的确诊人数为13人，其中11人与患者有过直接接触，或者是从武汉返美的。
So far, 13 people have been diagnosed in the United States, 11 of whom have had direct contact with patients or returned to the United States from Wuhan.
梅松尼耶表示，疾病控制与预防中心在检查症状或在和受感染人群有接触的人群中寻找病毒携带者方面采取了比一般情况下更加积极主动的措施。
The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention has been more proactive than usual in detecting symptoms or finding people living with the virus among people who come into contact with infected people, he said.
但这并不意味着疫情不会蔓延到美国。
But that does not mean the epidemic will not spread to the United States.
“疫情是否存在演变成全球性流行病的风险？这种风险绝对存在，”美国国家过敏症与传染病研究所(National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases)的安东尼·福奇(Anthony Fauci)博士说。
"Is there a risk of a global epidemic? There is an absolute risk," says Dr. Anthony Fauci of the National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases in the US.
美国目前暂时禁止过去14天内到过中国的外国公民入境，还对近期去过湖北省的美国公民及获得永久居住权的人进行了隔离，这是一项备受争议的举措。
The United States is temporarily banning the entry of foreign citizens who have been to China in the past 14 days, and isolating US citizens who have recently been to Hubei province and those who have been granted permanent residence is a controversial move.
梅松尼耶称，这一举措并没有将美国与病毒“完全隔离”，症状不明显或没有症状的人也可能传播病毒，但此举可以为美国卫生系统争取一些时间来做应对。
Mesonnier said the move did not "completely isolate" the United States from the virus, and people with less obvious or no symptoms could spread the virus, but it could buy time for the US health system to respond.
疫苗什么时候能研制出来？美国国家卫生研究院(National Institutes of Health)和其他一些卫生机构已经开始研究疫苗。
When will a vaccine be developed? The National Institutes of Health and other health authorities have begun studying vaccines.
在非紧急情况下，研制疫苗需要五到八年的时间，虽然这次花费的时间不会这么久，但福奇提醒人们也不要认为这次速度会快得多。
It takes five to eight years to develop a vaccine in a non-emergency situation, and while it won't take that long, Mr. Fauci cautions people not to think it will happen much faster.
“虽然这次我们将在三个月内进行疫苗试验，并可能在六个月内获得数据，但至少在一年内疫苗还不能作为综合应对措施的一部分，”福奇说。
"Although we will be conducting vaccine trials within three months and may have data within six months, the vaccine will not be part of an integrated response for at least a year," said Fauci.
他还称，如果疫苗有效，那么就要批量生产，而这一过程和研制疫苗一样麻烦。
If the vaccine works, it will have to be mass-produced, a process just as cumbersome as developing a vaccine, he said.
梅松尼耶称，专家们对这种病毒感到担忧的部分原因在于，如果疫情真的开始在美国蔓延，除了告诉人们不要外出、要勤洗手、避免大型集会以外，没有其他应对措施，而让人们不要外出这些措施的实施难度都比较大。
In part, experts are worried about the virus because there is no alternative to telling people not to go out, wash their hands and avoid large gatherings if the epidemic really starts to spread in the U.S., which makes it more difficult for people not to go out, he said.
和之前的流行病相比，这次疫情有多严重？新冠病毒疫情的死亡率略高于2%，而非典的死亡率为9%至10%，但二者传播方式不一样，福奇说。
How serious is the outbreak compared to previous epidemics? The death rate from the new crown virus epidemic is just over 2 percent, compared to 9 percent to 10 percent for SARS, but the two are spread differently, Forge said.
更具可比性的是流感，季节性流感的死亡率约为0.1%，1957年和1968年大范围传播的流感的死亡率为1%，1918年大范围传播的流感的死亡率接近2%。
More comparable is influenza, which has a mortality rate of about 0.1 per cent for seasonal influenza, 1 per cent for widespread influenza in 1957 and 1968, and nearly 2 per cent for generalized influenza in 1918.
福奇表示，他预计新冠病毒的死亡率比大范围传播的流感的死亡率“低几倍”——死亡率可能降至1%或更低——但他提醒说这只是一种可能，目前还没人说得准。
Fauci said he expected the death rate from the new strain of the virus to be "several times lower" than that from widespread influenza - a rate that could fall to 1 per cent or less - but cautioned that it was a possibility that no one could say for sure.
福奇称，美国国家卫生研究院提出向中国派出研究人员，中方目前还没有回复，美国疾病控制与预防中心目前也还没有安排人员加入当地的应急小组。
China has yet to respond to a request from the National Institutes of Health to send researchers to China, and the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention has yet to assign staff to local emergency response teams, Fauci said.
美国正遭遇十年来最严重的的流感，感染人数约为2200万，比感染新冠病毒的人数高出很多。
The United States is suffering its worst flu pandemic in a decade, with about 22 million people infected, far more than the number of people infected with the new crown virus.
但和新冠病毒不同的是，针对流感的对策是可行的，而且专业医疗人员对此也有多年的经验。
But unlike the new crown virus, a response to the flu is feasible, and many years of professional medical experience are involved.
福奇称，目前人们还不清楚新冠病毒的威力到底有多大以及病毒会如何演化。
It is unclear how powerful the new crown virus is and how it will evolve, Forge said.
翻译 ：小彩。
Little colourful.
